The paper focuses on hyperparameter tuning of machine learning algorithms, specifically decision trees, which is a common topic in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of optimization techniques to find the best hyperparameter configurations, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the relevance of hyperparameters using classification datasets, which is related to data mining (cs.DM). The use of decision trees for classification tasks is also relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE).
